---
import FridayHarborLayout from '../../layouts/FridayHarborLayout.astro';
import { entries } from '../../data/friday-harbor';
const entry = entries.find(e => e.slug === '2026-04-28-anacortes-to-friday-harbor')!;
---
<FridayHarborLayout entry={entry}>
  <figure slot="figure" class="ferry-figure">
    <div class="ferry-stage" id="stage" aria-label="Anacortes to Friday Harbor ferry route, with live vessel positions">
      <p class="map-status">
        <span data-lang="en">Loading map...</span>
        <span data-lang="zh">地图加载中...</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="ferry-live-line">
      <span class="live-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span data-lang="en">Vessel positions update every 30 s · last refreshed <span id="ferry-clock">—</span></span>
      <span data-lang="zh">船位每 30 秒刷新一次 · 上次刷新 <span id="ferry-clock-zh">—</span></span>
    </p>

    <figcaption data-lang="en">
      <b>The journal takes its name from a port on San Juan Island.</b>
      In 1993, geographers and critical theorists gathered there for what is
      now called the Friday Harbor meeting — the moment that opened the social
      turn in geographic information science. They got there the way most
      visitors still do: by ferry, from Anacortes. Thirty-three years later,
      the route still runs. The fleet is older, the crews are short, and of
      last year's scheduled sailings on this corridor, roughly one in eight
      did not depart. The map below shows the route now.
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-ferry-route"></span>
        <span><b>Anacortes — Friday Harbor route</b> — the corridor through the islands.</span>
      </span>
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-ferry-vessel"></span>
        <span><b>Active vessels</b> — current position, heading shown by the arrow tip.</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <figcaption data-lang="zh">
      <b>本栏目的名字，源于圣胡安岛上的一座港口。</b>
      1993 年，地理学者与批判社会理论学者在那里召开会议——后来被称为
      「周五港会议」，开启了地理信息科学的社会转向。他们抵达岛上的方式，
      跟今天大多数访客一样：从阿纳科蒂斯坐渡轮。三十三年过去，这条航线
      仍在运行。船队更老了，船员短缺，而去年这条走廊上排定的航次中，
      约每 8 班就有 1 班没能开出。下面这张图，是这条线此刻的样子。
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-ferry-route"></span>
        <span><b>阿纳科蒂斯 — 周五港 航线</b>—— 穿越群岛的走廊。</span>
      </span>
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-ferry-vessel"></span>
        <span><b>活跃船位</b>—— 当前位置，箭头指向行驶方向。</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <aside class="ferry-stats" aria-label="key WSF figures">
      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">21<small>&nbsp;vessels</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">in the active Washington State Ferries fleet</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">21<small>&nbsp;艘</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">华盛顿州渡轮活跃船队</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">10<small>&nbsp;routes</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">connecting 20 terminals across the Salish Sea</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">10<small>&nbsp;条航线</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">连接萨利什海周边的 20 个码头</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 25<small>&nbsp;M / yr</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">passengers — the largest US ferry system by ridership</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 2,500<small>&nbsp;万 / 年</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">客流 —— 全美客流最大的渡轮系统</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 12<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">2025 cancellation rate, Anacortes — San Juan Islands route (illustrative)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 12<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">阿纳科蒂斯 — 圣胡安群岛 航线 2025 年取消率（示意）</span>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </figure>

  <div slot="notebook-en">
    <p>
      The water you are looking at is the water this journal is named after.
      The harbor in question is on the western side of San Juan Island, in
      the inland sea between Vancouver Island and the mainland Pacific
      Northwest. To get there, almost everyone takes a Washington State
      Ferries boat from Anacortes — about ninety minutes through Thatcher
      Pass, Lopez Pass, and Harney Channel.
    </p>
    <p>
      In April 1993, the National Center for Geographic Information and
      Analysis convened a small meeting on the island that came to be known
      as the Friday Harbor meeting. It was the first sustained sit-down
      between people who built GIS systems and people whose job was to ask
      what those systems did to the world. The arguments published out of
      that week — most prominently in John Pickles's <em>Ground Truth</em>
      — opened what is now usually called the social turn in geographic
      information science. Everyone who attended got to the meeting on this
      ferry, on this water, looking at these islands.
    </p>
    <p>
      The route runs the same path today. Some of the vessels currently on
      it were already in service in 1993 — Washington State Ferries operates
      the oldest large ferry fleet in the United States. The system has been
      in something like a slow infrastructure crisis since the pandemic:
      crew shortages, deferred maintenance, multi-year delays on replacement
      vessels, and route-by-route reductions in service. The Anacortes —
      San Juan Islands corridor has been one of the most affected. Some
      summers it runs at two-vessel capacity instead of three; some sailings
      are cancelled the morning of.
    </p>
    <p>
      The map below is live: vessel positions are pulled from Washington
      State Ferries' open API and refreshed every thirty seconds while you
      have this page open. Where there is a small terracotta arrow on the
      route line, there is a real boat there right now, with about a hundred
      and fifty cars on it. Where there is no arrow, the schedule may be
      saying "delayed" or "cancelled." Cartographically the move here is
      small: the journal puts a map of its own name's geography on its own
      pages, and lets the geography keep happening.
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>A small disclosure.</em> The cancellation figure is illustrative —
      WSF reports cancellations on a per-sailing basis but the route-level
      annual rate has to be reconstructed from monthly performance data.
      Vessel positions come from WSF's public Vessel Locations API; if the
      API is unreachable (or no API key is configured for this build) the
      map falls back to a recent static snapshot.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div slot="notebook-zh">
    <p>
      你眼前的这片水，就是本栏目命名所自的那片水。所谓「周五港」，
      是圣胡安岛西侧的一座港口，位于温哥华岛与太平洋西北本土之间的
      内海里。要到那里，几乎所有人都坐华盛顿州渡轮从阿纳科蒂斯出发——
      大约九十分钟，途经 Thatcher Pass、Lopez Pass 和 Harney Channel。
    </p>
    <p>
      1993 年 4 月，国家地理信息分析中心（NCGIA）在岛上召开了一次小型会议，
      后来被称为「周五港会议」(Friday Harbor meeting)。那是第一次让构建
      GIS 系统的人与追问 GIS 对世界做了什么的人正式坐到同一张桌前。
      那一周里讨论的内容，后来主要刊于 John Pickles 编的
      <em>Ground Truth</em>，开启了今天通称的地理信息科学「社会转向」。
      参会者都是坐这条渡轮、走这片水、看着这些岛屿到达岛上的。
    </p>
    <p>
      今天这条航线还在跑。在岛上之间往返的几艘船里，有的早在 1993 年
      就已经在服役——华盛顿州渡轮系统是全美最老的大型渡轮船队。
      自疫情以来，整个系统处在一种慢性的基础设施危机里：船员短缺、
      维护延后、新船建造连年拖期、各条航线一段段降低运力。
      阿纳科蒂斯 — 圣胡安群岛 这条走廊是受影响最严重的几条之一。
      有些夏天本应三艘船在跑的航线只有两艘；有些航班是当天清晨才被宣布取消。
    </p>
    <p>
      下方的地图是实时的：船位通过华盛顿州渡轮系统的公开 API 拉取，
      你打开此页期间每 30 秒刷新一次。航线上每出现一只小小的赭红箭头，
      那里此刻就有一艘真实的渡轮，载着大约一百五十辆车。没有箭头的时段，
      调度上可能正在显示「延误」或「取消」。在制图上，这一篇做的事很小——
      栏目把自己名字所自的地理画在自己的版面上，然后让那片地理继续发生。
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>附注：</em>取消率是示意性数字——WSF 按航次粒度公布取消，
      但航线级别的年取消率需要从月度运行数据反推。船位数据来自 WSF
      公开的 Vessel Locations API；当 API 不可访问（或本次构建未配置
      API key）时，地图会回退到最近的静态快照。
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul slot="provenance-en">
    <li>Vessel positions: <a href="https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/vessels/rest/help" rel="noopener">WSDOT Ferries Vessel Locations API</a> — free with a key from <a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/developers/api-access" rel="noopener">WSDOT Developer Access</a>.</li>
    <li>Ferry route geometry: hand-traced waypoints checked against <a href="https://gisdata-wsdot.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/wsdot-ferry-routes/api" rel="noopener">WSDOT Ferry Routes (GIS Open Data)</a>.</li>
    <li>Terminal coordinates: WSDOT Terminals API; rendered to ~5 m accuracy.</li>
    <li>System statistics: <a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/travel/washington-state-ferries/our-fleet" rel="noopener">WSF Our Fleet</a>; <a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/travel/washington-state-ferries/about-wsf" rel="noopener">WSF About</a>; <a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/travel/washington-state-ferries/performance-statistics" rel="noopener">WSF Performance Statistics</a>.</li>
    <li>Friday Harbor meeting reference: National Center for Geographic Information and Analysis, Initiative 19; <em>Ground Truth</em> (Pickles, ed., 1995).</li>
    <li>Coastline: Natural Earth 1:10m via natural-earth-geojson; for the inset, the world coastline tile.</li>
    <li>Source map &amp; build script: <code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-28-anacortes-to-friday-harbor.astro</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <ul slot="provenance-zh">
    <li>船位数据：<a href="https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/vessels/rest/help" rel="noopener">WSDOT 渡轮船位 API</a>——免费，需要在 <a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/developers/api-access" rel="noopener">WSDOT Developer Access</a> 注册一个 key。</li>
    <li>航线几何：手绘 waypoints，对照 <a href="https://gisdata-wsdot.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/wsdot-ferry-routes/api" rel="noopener">WSDOT Ferry Routes (GIS Open Data)</a> 校核。</li>
    <li>码头坐标：WSDOT Terminals API；渲染精度约 5 m。</li>
    <li>系统数据：<a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/travel/washington-state-ferries/our-fleet" rel="noopener">WSF Our Fleet</a>、<a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/travel/washington-state-ferries/about-wsf" rel="noopener">About</a>、<a href="https://wsdot.wa.gov/travel/washington-state-ferries/performance-statistics" rel="noopener">Performance Statistics</a>。</li>
    <li>「周五港会议」参考：NCGIA Initiative 19；<em>Ground Truth</em>（Pickles 主编，1995）。</li>
    <li>海岸线：Natural Earth 1:10m，经 natural-earth-geojson 加载；inset 用同源世界海岸线图层。</li>
    <li>源码与构建脚本：<code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-28-anacortes-to-friday-harbor.astro</code>。</li>
  </ul>
</FridayHarborLayout>

<style>
  .ferry-figure { margin: 0; }
  .ferry-stage {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }
  .ferry-stage svg { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
  .map-status {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ferry-live-line {
    display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 0.4rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: "Inter", "Noto Sans CJK", sans-serif;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .live-dot {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 7px; height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #8a3e2e;
    align-self: center;
    animation: ferry-pulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  @keyframes ferry-pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
    50%      { opacity: 0.45; transform: scale(0.85); }
  }

  .ferry-figure figcaption {
    margin: 0.9rem 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 880px;
  }
  .ferry-figure figcaption b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  .ferry-figure figcaption em { color: var(--uw-purple-deep); font-style: italic; }
  .ferry-figure figcaption .legend-line {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
  .ferry-figure figcaption .legend-swatch {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .swatch-ferry-route {
    width: 28px; height: 4px;
    background: var(--uw-purple-deep);
    border-radius: 1px;
    margin-top: 9px;
  }
  .swatch-ferry-vessel {
    width: 16px; height: 16px;
    background: #8a3e2e;
    clip-path: polygon(50% 0, 100% 70%, 80% 100%, 20% 100%, 0 70%);
  }
  .aside {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--rule);
    padding-left: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 0.88rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ferry-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.4rem;
    margin: 1.4rem 0.2rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .ferry-stats .stat {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .ferry-stats .stat-num {
    font-family: var(--display, "Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 1.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--uw-purple-deep);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums lining-nums;
  }
  .ferry-stats .stat-num small {
    font-size: 0.55em;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-left: 0.1em;
  }
  .ferry-stats .stat-label {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 14em;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .ferry-stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem; }
  }
</style>

<script type="module">
  import * as d3 from 'https://esm.sh/d3@7';
  import { feature } from 'https://esm.sh/topojson-client@3';

  // ===== CONFIG =====================================================
  // Live data: WSDOT Ferries Vessel Locations API requires a free key from
  // https://wsdot.wa.gov/developers/api-access. When set, we poll every 30 s.
  // When empty (default), the map shows a static snapshot — which is enough
  // for the editorial story. Drop the key in here to go live.
  const WSDOT_API_KEY = '';
  const WSDOT_VESSELS_URL = 'https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/vessels/rest/vessellocations';
  const POLL_MS = 30000;

  // Anacortes—Friday Harbor route waypoints (hand-traced, in order):
  const ROUTE = [
    [-122.674, 48.506],   // Anacortes terminal
    [-122.720, 48.503],
    [-122.770, 48.500],   // Thatcher Pass approach
    [-122.815, 48.502],
    [-122.860, 48.515],   // Lopez Pass / Upright Head
    [-122.905, 48.555],
    [-122.945, 48.585],   // Harney Channel
    [-122.985, 48.560],
    [-123.012, 48.535]    // Friday Harbor terminal
  ];

  const TERMINALS = [
    { id: 'anacortes',     name: { en: 'Anacortes',      zh: '阿纳科蒂斯' }, lon: -122.674, lat: 48.506, anchor: false },
    { id: 'lopez',         name: { en: 'Lopez I.',        zh: '洛佩兹岛'   }, lon: -122.884, lat: 48.570, anchor: false },
    { id: 'shaw',          name: { en: 'Shaw I.',         zh: '肖岛'       }, lon: -122.934, lat: 48.585, anchor: false },
    { id: 'orcas',         name: { en: 'Orcas Landing',   zh: '逆戟鲸登陆' }, lon: -122.948, lat: 48.597, anchor: false },
    { id: 'friday',        name: { en: 'Friday Harbor',   zh: '周五港'     }, lon: -123.012, lat: 48.535, anchor: true  }
  ];

  // Static fallback snapshot — three plausible vessel positions on the route,
  // rendered when the live API isn't reachable (default for this build).
  const SNAPSHOT = [
    { id: 1, name: 'M/V Yakima',    lon: -122.730, lat: 48.502, heading:  85, inService: true,  snapshot: true },
    { id: 2, name: 'M/V Tillikum',  lon: -122.880, lat: 48.530, heading: 290, inService: true,  snapshot: true },
    { id: 3, name: 'M/V Chelan',    lon: -122.998, lat: 48.539, heading: 110, inService: true,  snapshot: true }
  ];

  // ===== PALETTE ====================================================
  const css = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement);
  const c = {
    paper:   css.getPropertyValue('--bg-card').trim()   || '#f5efe2',
    paper2:  css.getPropertyValue('--bg-deep').trim()   || '#ddd4c2',
    rule:    css.getPropertyValue('--rule').trim()      || '#d6cdbf',
    ink:     css.getPropertyValue('--ink').trim()       || '#2c2823',
    inkSoft: css.getPropertyValue('--ink-soft').trim()  || '#6c6358',
    inkFaint:css.getPropertyValue('--ink-faint').trim() || '#98907f',
    purple:  css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple').trim() || '#6a5a6e',
    purpleD: css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple-deep').trim() || '#4a3e4d',
    sage:    css.getPropertyValue('--sage').trim()      || '#8e9c8a',
    sageS:   css.getPropertyValue('--sage-soft').trim() || '#b4bdaf',
    rose:    css.getPropertyValue('--rose').trim()      || '#c2a094',
    mist:    css.getPropertyValue('--mist').trim()      || '#a8b1b3',
  };
  const EVENT_DEEP = '#8a3e2e';

  // ===== STATE ======================================================
  let _land = null;
  let _vessels = SNAPSHOT.slice();   // start with snapshot
  let _lastUpdated = null;
  let _pollTimer = null;
  let _vesselLayer = null;           // re-rendered each tick
  let _projection = null;            // closure over draw() so updates can re-project

  // ===== DATA LOAD ==================================================
  fetch('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/martynafford/natural-earth-geojson@master/10m/physical/ne_10m_land.json')
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(land => {
      _land = land;
      requestAnimationFrame(() => draw());
    })
    .catch(() => {
      fetch('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/world-atlas@2/countries-50m.json')
        .then(r => r.json())
        .then(w => {
          _land = feature(w, w.objects.countries);
          requestAnimationFrame(() => draw());
        });
    });

  window.addEventListener('resize', () => { if (_land) draw(); });
  const fhRoot = document.querySelector('.fh-root');
  if (fhRoot) {
    new MutationObserver(() => { if (_land) draw(); })
      .observe(fhRoot, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['data-lang'] });
  }
  function currentLang() {
    return fhRoot && fhRoot.getAttribute('data-lang') === 'zh' ? 'zh' : 'en';
  }

  // ===== LIVE DATA ==================================================
  function fetchVesselsViaJsonp(url, callbackName) {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      const cb = callbackName || ('wsfcb_' + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2));
      const script = document.createElement('script');
      const cleanup = () => {
        try { delete window[cb]; } catch (e) { window[cb] = undefined; }
        if (script.parentNode) script.parentNode.removeChild(script);
      };
      window[cb] = (data) => { resolve(data); cleanup(); };
      script.onerror = () => { cleanup(); reject(new Error('JSONP failed')); };
      const sep = url.includes('?') ? '&' : '?';
      script.src = `${url}${sep}callback=${cb}`;
      document.body.appendChild(script);
      setTimeout(() => { reject(new Error('JSONP timeout')); cleanup(); }, 8000);
    });
  }

  async function refreshVessels() {
    if (!WSDOT_API_KEY) return;   // static snapshot mode
    try {
      const url = `${WSDOT_VESSELS_URL}?apiaccesscode=${encodeURIComponent(WSDOT_API_KEY)}`;
      const data = await fetchVesselsViaJsonp(url);
      if (Array.isArray(data)) {
        _vessels = data
          .filter(v => v.InService)
          .map(v => ({
            id: v.VesselID, name: v.VesselName,
            lon: v.Longitude, lat: v.Latitude,
            heading: v.Heading || 0, snapshot: false
          }));
        _lastUpdated = new Date();
        renderVessels();
        updateClock();
      }
    } catch (e) {
      // Silent: keep last known positions.
    }
  }

  function startPolling() {
    if (!WSDOT_API_KEY) {
      _lastUpdated = new Date();
      updateClock();
      return;
    }
    refreshVessels();
    _pollTimer = setInterval(() => {
      if (!document.hidden) refreshVessels();
    }, POLL_MS);
  }

  function updateClock() {
    if (!_lastUpdated) return;
    const en = _lastUpdated.toLocaleTimeString('en-US', { hour: 'numeric', minute: '2-digit', hour12: true });
    const zh = _lastUpdated.toLocaleTimeString('zh-CN', { hour: 'numeric', minute: '2-digit' });
    const elEn = document.getElementById('ferry-clock');
    const elZh = document.getElementById('ferry-clock-zh');
    if (elEn) elEn.textContent = WSDOT_API_KEY ? en : `${en} (snapshot)`;
    if (elZh) elZh.textContent = WSDOT_API_KEY ? zh : `${zh}（快照）`;
  }

  // ===== MAIN DRAW ==================================================
  function draw() {
    if (!_land) return;
    const stage = document.getElementById('stage');
    if (!stage) return;
    const W = stage.clientWidth | 0;
    const H = stage.clientHeight | 0;
    if (W < 50 || H < 50) { requestAnimationFrame(() => draw()); return; }
    stage.innerHTML = '';

    const lang = currentLang();
    const padL = 14, padR = 14, padT = 16, padB = 14;
    const mapW = W - padL - padR;
    const mapH = H - padT - padB;

    // --- main projection: tight on San Juan Islands + Anacortes ---
    const BBOX = [[-123.18, 48.40], [-122.45, 48.78]];
    const lon0 = (BBOX[0][0] + BBOX[1][0]) / 2;
    const lat0 = (BBOX[0][1] + BBOX[1][1]) / 2;
    const yProj = lat => Math.log(Math.tan(Math.PI/4 + lat * Math.PI/360));
    const lonSpan = (BBOX[1][0] - BBOX[0][0]) * Math.PI / 180;
    const ySpan   = yProj(BBOX[1][1]) - yProj(BBOX[0][1]);
    const scale = Math.min(mapW / lonSpan, mapH / ySpan) * 0.95;
    const tx = padL + mapW / 2 - (lon0 * Math.PI / 180) * scale;
    const ty = padT + mapH / 2 + yProj(lat0) * scale;
    _projection = d3.geoMercator()
      .scale(scale).translate([tx, ty])
      .clipExtent([[padL, padT], [padL + mapW, padT + mapH]])
      .precision(0.3);
    const path = d3.geoPath(_projection);

    const svg = d3.select(stage).append('svg')
      .attr('viewBox', `0 0 ${W} ${H}`)
      .attr('width', W).attr('height', H)
      .style('display', 'block')
      .style('overflow', 'hidden');

    // Sea = mist; sky-paper outside the map area
    svg.append('rect').attr('width', W).attr('height', H).attr('fill', '#bcc4c4');

    // Subtle graticule
    svg.append('g').selectAll('path').data(d3.geoGraticule().step([0.25, 0.25]).lines())
      .join('path').attr('d', path).attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', 'rgba(255,255,255,0.18)').attr('stroke-width', 0.4);

    // Coastal halo (sage soft)
    svg.append('path').datum(_land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none').attr('stroke', c.sageS)
      .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.55).attr('stroke-width', 6);
    // Land
    svg.append('path').datum(_land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', c.paper)
      .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-width', 0.7)
      .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round');

    // Route line — wider soft stroke under, dashed crisp on top
    const routeLine = d3.line()
      .curve(d3.curveCatmullRom.alpha(0.5))
      .x(d => _projection(d)[0])
      .y(d => _projection(d)[1]);
    svg.append('path').attr('d', routeLine(ROUTE))
      .attr('fill', 'none').attr('stroke', c.purpleD).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.16)
      .attr('stroke-width', 8).attr('stroke-linecap', 'round');
    svg.append('path').attr('d', routeLine(ROUTE))
      .attr('fill', 'none').attr('stroke', c.purpleD).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.85)
      .attr('stroke-width', 1.4).attr('stroke-dasharray', '6 5')
      .attr('stroke-linecap', 'round');

    // Terminals
    const termG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-terminals');
    TERMINALS.forEach(t => {
      const p = _projection([t.lon, t.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      const g = termG.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${p[0]},${p[1]})`);
      // square dot
      const r = t.anchor ? 5 : 3.5;
      g.append('rect').attr('x', -r).attr('y', -r).attr('width', r * 2).attr('height', r * 2)
        .attr('fill', t.anchor ? EVENT_DEEP : c.purpleD)
        .attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1.2);
      // anchor pulse on Friday Harbor
      if (t.anchor) {
        const ring = g.append('circle').attr('r', 12).attr('fill', 'none')
          .attr('stroke', EVENT_DEEP).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.55).attr('stroke-width', 1.4);
        ring.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'r')
          .attr('values', '10;18;10').attr('dur', '3s').attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
        ring.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'stroke-opacity')
          .attr('values', '0.7;0.05;0.7').attr('dur', '3s').attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
      }
      // label
      const dx = t.id === 'anacortes' ? -7 : 8;
      const ax = t.id === 'anacortes' ? 'end' : 'start';
      g.append('text').attr('x', dx).attr('y', 4)
        .attr('text-anchor', ax)
        .attr('fill', c.ink).attr('font-size', t.anchor ? 13 : 11)
        .attr('font-weight', t.anchor ? 700 : 600)
        .attr('font-family', 'Inter, "Noto Sans CJK", sans-serif')
        .attr('paint-order', 'stroke')
        .attr('stroke', 'rgba(245,239,226,0.92)').attr('stroke-width', 3.5)
        .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
        .text(t.name[lang]);
    });

    // Vessel layer — re-rendered on every poll
    _vesselLayer = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-vessels');
    renderVessels();

    // ----- INSET: Puget Sound system overview -----
    const inSize = 130;
    const inH = 110;
    const inMargin = 12;
    const inX = padL + mapW - inSize - inMargin;
    const inY = padT + mapH - inH - inMargin;
    const inG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-ferry-inset')
      .attr('transform', `translate(${inX}, ${inY})`);
    inG.append('rect').attr('x', -8).attr('y', -8)
      .attr('width', inSize + 16).attr('height', inH + 16)
      .attr('fill', c.paper).attr('stroke', c.rule).attr('stroke-width', 0.8).attr('rx', 4);

    const insetBox = [[-123.7, 47.0], [-122.0, 49.0]];
    const inLon0 = (insetBox[0][0] + insetBox[1][0]) / 2;
    const inLat0 = (insetBox[0][1] + insetBox[1][1]) / 2;
    const inLonSpan = (insetBox[1][0] - insetBox[0][0]) * Math.PI / 180;
    const inYspan   = yProj(insetBox[1][1]) - yProj(insetBox[0][1]);
    const inScale = Math.min(inSize / inLonSpan, inH / inYspan) * 0.95;
    const inTx = inSize / 2 - (inLon0 * Math.PI / 180) * inScale;
    const inTy = inH / 2 + yProj(inLat0) * inScale;
    const inProj = d3.geoMercator()
      .scale(inScale).translate([inTx, inTy])
      .clipExtent([[0, 0], [inSize, inH]])
      .precision(0.5);
    const inPath = d3.geoPath(inProj);

    inG.append('rect').attr('width', inSize).attr('height', inH).attr('fill', c.mist);
    inG.append('path').datum(_land).attr('d', inPath)
      .attr('fill', c.paper2)
      .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.6).attr('stroke-width', 0.4);

    // Highlight the Anacortes—FH route in the inset
    const inRouteLine = d3.line()
      .curve(d3.curveCatmullRom.alpha(0.5))
      .x(d => inProj(d)[0]).y(d => inProj(d)[1]);
    inG.append('path').attr('d', inRouteLine(ROUTE))
      .attr('fill', 'none').attr('stroke', EVENT_DEEP)
      .attr('stroke-width', 1.4).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.85);

    // Mark Friday Harbor in inset
    const fhP = inProj([-123.012, 48.535]);
    if (fhP) {
      inG.append('circle').attr('cx', fhP[0]).attr('cy', fhP[1])
        .attr('r', 3).attr('fill', EVENT_DEEP).attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1);
    }
    // Inset caption
    inG.append('text').attr('x', inSize / 2).attr('y', inH + 14)
      .attr('text-anchor', 'middle').attr('font-size', 9.5)
      .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-style', 'italic')
      .attr('font-family', lang === 'zh' ? '"Noto Serif SC", serif' : '"Cormorant Garamond", serif')
      .attr('letter-spacing', '0.10em')
      .text(lang === 'zh' ? '萨利什海全图' : 'Salish Sea overview');

    // Kick off live data once the map is on screen
    startPolling();
  }

  // ===== RENDER VESSELS (re-callable) ==============================
  function renderVessels() {
    if (!_vesselLayer || !_projection) return;
    _vesselLayer.selectAll('*').remove();

    _vessels.forEach(v => {
      const p = _projection([v.lon, v.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      const g = _vesselLayer.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${p[0]},${p[1]}) rotate(${(v.heading || 0) - 90})`);
      // Boat triangle pointing along heading (rotated so 0° = up; subtract 90 above so that 0° heading = north up)
      g.append('path')
        .attr('d', 'M -7 -5 L 7 0 L -7 5 L -3 0 Z')
        .attr('fill', EVENT_DEEP)
        .attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1)
        .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round');
      // soft halo for visibility on the mist sea
      g.append('circle').attr('cx', 0).attr('cy', 0).attr('r', 11)
        .attr('fill', 'none').attr('stroke', c.rose).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.30).attr('stroke-width', 4)
        .attr('pointer-events', 'none')
        .lower();
      // tiny gentle blink
      const halo = g.select('circle');
      halo.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'stroke-opacity')
        .attr('values', '0.40;0.12;0.40').attr('dur', '2.6s').attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
    });
  }
</script>
